{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532266870,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_MSvYqLUtzuCnUKKIW7wziBEH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"authoring boundary|DESIGN.md|tokens.json|extract|validate|style reference|fidelity","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 55 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/taste-skill.md:\n  Line 456:           invalidateOnRefresh: true,\n\n  Line 584: * **Brand fidelity** - primary brand color stays recognisable. Don't desaturate the brand into a dark mode.\n\n  Line 789: * **Redesign - Preserve** - modernise without breaking the brand. Audit first, extract brand tokens, evolve gradually.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/bencium-innovative-ux-designer.md:\n  Line 398:      - **Pattern consistency**: All forms validate on blur and submit\n\n  Line 718: - RESPONSIVE-DESIGN.md - Mobile-first breakpoints and patterns\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/polish.md:\n  Line 200: - [ ] All forms properly labeled and validated\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/critique.md:\n  Line 498: | 1 | Few safeguards; some inputs validated, most aren't |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/fixing-motion-performance.md:\n  Line 99: - validate layer behavior with tooling when performance matters\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/harden.md:\n  Line 331: - Assume perfect input (validate everything)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/overdrive.md:\n  Line 15: Push an interface past conventional limits. This isn't just about visual effects. It's about using the full power of the browser to make any part of an interface feel extraordinary: a table that handles a million rows, a dialog that morphs from its trigger, a form that validates in real-time with streaming feedback, a page transition that feels cinematic.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/stitch-skill.md:\n  Line 3: description: Semantic Design System Skill for Google Stitch. Generates agent-friendly DESIGN.md files that enforce premium, anti-generic UI standards вҖ” strict typography, calibrated color, asymmetric layouts, perpetual micro-motion, and hardware-accelerated performance.\n\n  Line 9: This skill generates `DESIGN.md` files optimized for Google Stitch screen generation. It translates the battle-tested anti-slop frontend engineering directives into Stitch's native semantic design language вҖ” descriptive, natural-language rules paired with precise values that Stitch's AI agent can interpret to produce premium, non-generic interfaces.\n\n  Line 11: The generated `DESIGN.md` serves as the **single source of truth** for prompting Stitch to generate new screens that align with a curated, high-agency design language. Stitch interprets design through **\"Visual Descriptions\"** supported by specific color values, typography specs, and component behaviors.\n\n  Line 18: Generate a `DESIGN.md` file that encodes:\n\n  Line 97: Encode these as explicit \"NEVER DO\" rules in the DESIGN.md:\n\n  Line 115: ## Output Format (DESIGN.md Structure)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/impeccable.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Use when the user wants to design, redesign, shape, critique, audit, polish, clarify, distill, harden, optimize, adapt, animate, colorize, extract, or otherwise improve a frontend interface. Covers websites, landing pages, dashboards, product UI, app shells, components, forms, settings, onboarding, and empty states. Handles UX review, visual hierarchy, information architecture, cognitive load, accessibility, performance, responsive behavior, theming, anti-patterns, typography, fonts, spacing, layout, alignment, color, motion, micro-interactions, UX copy, error states, edge cases, i18n, and reusable design systems or tokens. Also use for bland designs that need to become bolder or more delightful, loud designs that should become quieter, live browser iteration on UI elements, or ambitious visual effects that should feel technically extraordinary. Not for backend-only or non-UI tasks.\"\n\n  Line 17: 1. Run `node {{scripts_path}}/context.mjs` once per session. If the request names or implies a file, route, or app inside a monorepo, infer the concrete path and run `node {{scripts_path}}/context.mjs --target <path>` instead. If you've already seen its output in this conversation, do not re-run it. The script either prints the project's PRODUCT.md (and DESIGN.md when present) as a markdown block, or tells you it's missing. Follow whatever it prints. **If it reports `NO_PRODUCT_MD`, stop and follow `reference/init.md` before doing anything else.** If the output ends with an `UPDATE_AVAILABLE` directive, follow it (ask the user once about updating, then continue). It never blocks the current task.\n\n  Line 125: | `init` | Build | Set up project context: PRODUCT.md, DESIGN.md, live config, next steps | [reference/init.md](reference/init.md) |\n\n  Line 126: | `document` | Build | Generate DESIGN.md from existing project code | [reference/document.md](reference/document.md) |\n\n  Line 127: | `extract [target]` | Build | Pull reusable tokens and components into design system | [reference/extract.md](reference/extract.md) |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/frontend-slides.md:\n  Line 254: 1. **Extract content** вҖ” Run `python scripts/extract-pptx.py <input.pptx> <output_dir>` (install python-pptx if needed: `pip install python-pptx`)\n\n  Line 255: 2. **Confirm with user** вҖ” Present extracted slide titles, content summaries, and image counts\n\n  Line 378: | [scripts/extract-pptx.py](scripts/extract-pptx.py) | Python script for PPT content extraction                             | Phase 4 (conversion)      |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/ux-strategy/skills/information-architecture/SKILL.md:\n  Line 46: - Conduct open card sorts before designing new structures; closed card sorts to validate\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-research/README.md:\n  Line 17: - **survey-design** вҖ” Design surveys that collect reliable, unbiased quantitative data to validate hypotheses and measure user attitudes at scale.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/prototyping-testing/README.md:\n  Line 4: - **prototype-strategy** вҖ” Choose the right prototyping fidelity and method for the design question.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/prototyping-testing/commands/evaluate.md:\n  Line 16: Consider following up with `/test-plan` to validate findings with real users.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/prototyping-testing/commands/prototype-plan.md:\n  Line 8: 1. **Strategy** вҖ” Choose fidelity and method using `prototype-strategy` skill.\n\n  Line 15: Prototyping plan with fidelity rationale, user flows, wireframe specs, test scenarios, accessibility plan, and timeline.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-research/skills/summarize-interview/SKILL.md:\n  Line 3: description: Summarize a user interview transcript into structured insights with key themes, quotes, and action items. Use after conducting user interviews to extract and share findings efficiently.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/prototyping-testing/skills/prototype-strategy/SKILL.md:\n  Line 3: description: Choose the right prototyping fidelity and method for the design question.\n\n  Line 8: You help teams choose the right fidelity, tool, and method for prototyping based on what they need to learn.\n\n  Line 30: - Match fidelity to the question, not the deadline\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-research/skills/survey-design/SKILL.md:\n  Line 3: description: Design surveys that collect reliable, unbiased quantitative data to validate hypotheses and measure user attitudes at scale.\n\n  Line 12: - You need to validate or quantify findings from qualitative research (interviews, usability tests)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-research/skills/research-repository/SKILL.md:\n  Line 25: - **Confidence**: High (multiple studies, large sample) / Medium (single study, validated) / Low (one session, early signal)\n\n  Line 40: - **Status**: validated, superseded, conflicting\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-research/commands/interview.md:\n  Line 9: - If the user provides a **transcript**: Use the `summarize-interview` skill to extract themes, quotes, pain points, and action items.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-research/commands/synthesize.md:\n  Line 11: 4. After completion, suggest: \"Want me to `/discover` to create personas from these insights?\" or \"Want me to `/test-plan` to validate these findings with usability testing?\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/interaction-design/skills/form-design/SKILL.md:\n  Line 33: - **Inline validation**: validate on blur (when the user leaves the field), not on every keystroke вҖ” real-time validation on typing is distracting\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-systems/skills/localization-design/SKILL.md:\n  Line 23: - Navigation labels: test all nav items together at 130% length to validate menu doesn't break\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/ski