",\n      \"design quality score\",\n      \"P0 P1 design findings\",\n      \"extract design system\",\n      \"generate design.md\",\n      \"capture website css\",\n      \"design tokens from url\",\n      \"create design reference\",\n      \"design-to-markdown\",\n      \"extract design tokens\"\n    ],\n    \"key_topics\": [\n      \"sk-design\",\n      \"mode-registry\",\n      \"workflowMode\",\n      \"backendKind\",\n      \"reference-base\",\n      \"interface-mode\",\n      \"foundations-mode\",\n      \"motion-mode\",\n      \"audit-mode\",\n      \"md-generator-mode\",\n      \"shared-design-reference-base\",\n      \"anti-slop\",\n      \"design-token-vocabulary\",\n      \"cognitive-laws\"\n    ],\n    \"key_files\": [\n      \".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json\"\n    ],\n    \"entities\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"sk-design\",\n        \"kind\": \"skill\",\n        \"path\": \".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md\",\n        \"source\": \"derived\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"mode-registry\",\n        \"kind\": \"config\",\n        \"path\": \".opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json\",\n        \"source\": \"derived\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"causal_summary\": \"sk-design is the single public design skill that routes a request to one of five design modes (interface, foundations, motion, audit, md-generator) by workflowMode through mode-registry.json over a shared design reference base. The four doc-guidance modes cite the shared reference base (anti-slop principles, cognitive laws, design-token vocabulary) for consistent vocabulary, while md-generator runs its own Playwright CSS-extraction backend (backendKind discriminates the two). The hub holds no per-mode design logic; every mode keeps its own judgment, examples, and verification in its packet, and all five route by hub membership so the advisor sees exactly one design identity.\",\n    \"source_docs\": [\n      \"SKILL.md\",\n      \"mode-registry.json\"\n    ],\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-06-25T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"last_updated_at\": \"2026-06-26T00:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":159,"totalLines":159,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/graph-metadata.json","time":{"start":1782532433590,"end":1782532433599}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f9f392428e18d6d016a3f495163cc819498a7aaef38df2c0b"}},"id":"prt_f07366649001DijEw38w0HW69H","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","messageID":"msg_f073583cf001yFIFOrufYdGerR"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532433618,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Cm3Wqx0M5YOq4d5BCkihKUuJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/stripe/DESIGN.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/stripe/DESIGN.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Stripe вҖ” Style Reference\n2: > Indigo-violet rationed against a white field вҖ” borders carry the structure, one saturated blue carries the brand.\n3: \n4: **Theme:** light\n5: \n6: The canvas is pure Snow (`#ffffff`), and the system is built almost entirely from borders rather than fills вҖ” Ink (`#000000`) and a deep navy family draw nearly every line, frame, and divider on the page. A single saturated blue-violet, Azure (`#533afd`), is the brand signal: it owns link text, the primary CTA fill, and brand border accents, and almost nothing else competes with it. Body and UI text run in slate-blue tones (`#50617a`, `#64748d`) and deep navy (`#061b31`) rather than flat black, keeping the page tonal rather than high-contrast. Type is set in sohne-var across a wide variable range, with hierarchy carried by scale вҖ” a 56px display against a 16px body вҖ” and tightening letter-spacing as size grows. Depth is real but quiet: three shadow tokens, two of them tinted with the brand's own navy, give cards a soft chromatic lift instead of a hard drop shadow. Layout caps at 1266px on a spacious 4px-based rhythm, with section gaps stepping from 48px to 96px.\n7: \n8: ## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n9: \n10: | Name | Value | Token | Role |\n11: |------|-------|-------|------|\n12: | Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a near-black |\n13: | Azure | `#533afd` | `--color-azure` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a blue |\n14: | Azure 2 | `#50617a` | `--color-azure-2` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n15: | Deep Azure | `#061b31` | `--color-deep-azure` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a deep blue |\n16: | Snow | `#ffffff` | `--color-snow` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a near-white |\n17: | Azure 3 | `#64748d` | `--color-azure-3` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a blue |\n18: | Azure 4 | `#0000ee` | `--color-azure-4` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n19: | Azure 5 | `#3c4f69` | `--color-azure-5` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a blue |\n20: | Deep Azure 2 | `#273951` | `--color-deep-azure-2` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a deep blue |\n21: | Light Azure | `#e5edf5` | `--color-light-azure` | borders, backgrounds, gradients вҖ” a light blue |\n22: | Ember | `#ff6118` | `--color-ember` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a orange |\n23: | Deep Azure 3 | `#1a2c44` | `--color-deep-azure-3` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a deep blue |\n24: | Azure 6 | `#7389ff` | `--color-azure-6` | borders, text, gradients вҖ” a blue |\n25: | Azure 7 | `#7d8ba4` | `--color-azure-7` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n26: | Light Azure 2 | `#b9b9f9` | `--color-light-azure-2` | borders вҖ” a light blue |\n27: | Light Azure 3 | `#d6d9fc` | `--color-light-azure-3` | borders, gradients вҖ” a light blue |\n28: | Azure 8 | `#839bc8` | `--color-azure-8` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n29: | Azure 9 | `#7f7dfc` | `--color-azure-9` | borders, text, gradients вҖ” a blue |\n30: | Azure 10 | `#a3b5d6` | `--color-azure-10` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n31: | Ink 2 | `#101010` | `--color-ink-2` | borders, text вҖ” a near-black |\n32: | Light Azure 4 | `#e2e4ff` | `--color-light-azure-4` | borders, backgrounds, gradients вҖ” a light blue |\n33: | Voltage | `#81b81a` | `--color-voltage` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a green |\n34: | Azure 11 | `#000eff` | `--color-azure-11` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n35: | Azure 12 | `#2d2564` | `--color-azure-12` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n36: | Magenta | `#f44bcc` | `--color-magenta` | gradients вҖ” a magenta |\n37: | Deep Azure 4 | `#182659` | `--color-deep-azure-4` | borders, gradients вҖ” a deep blue |\n38: | Indigo | `#da4bfe` | `--color-indigo` | gradients вҖ” a indigo |\n39: | Obsidian | `#171717` | `--color-obsidian` | icons вҖ” a deep near-black |\n40: | Light Ember | `#ffe0d1` | `--color-light-ember` | backgrounds вҖ” a light orange |\n41: | Azure 13 | `#32325d` | `--color-azure-13` | decorative use вҖ” a blue |\n42: | Light Azure 5 | `#d4dee9` | `--color-light-azure-5` | borders, icons вҖ” a light blue |\n43: | Deep Azure 5 | `#031323` | `--color-deep-azure-5` | backgrounds, icons вҖ” a deep blue |\n44: | Ember 2 | `#ffcf5e` | `--color-ember-2` | gradients вҖ” a orange |\n45: | Indigo 2 | `#4304ea` | `--color-indigo-2` | gradients вҖ” a indigo |\n46: | Light Azure 6 | `#b4d8ff` | `--color-light-azure-6` | gradients вҖ” a light blue |\n47: | Crimson | `#ff8c6c` | `--color-crimson` | gradients вҖ” a red |\n48: | Ember 3 | `#fbbc04` | `--color-ember-3` | icons вҖ” a orange |\n49: | Light Ember 2 | `#faf1e5` | `--color-light-ember-2` | icons, gradients вҖ” a light orange |\n50: | Indigo 3 | `#c489ff` | `--color-indigo-3` | gradients вҖ” a indigo |\n51: | Ember 4 | `#ffc977` | `--color-ember-4` | gradients вҖ” a orange |\n52: | Azure 14 | `#715cff` | `--color-azure-14` | gradients вҖ” a blue |\n53: | Voltage 2 | `#00d66f` | `--color-voltage-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a green |\n54: | Deep Teal | `#0b3b45` | `--color-deep-teal` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep teal |\n55: | Azure 15 | `#4285f4` | `--color-azure-15` | icons вҖ” a blue |\n56: | Sage | `#34a853` | `--color-sage` | icons вҖ” a green-gray |\n57: | Crimson 2 | `#ea4335` | `--color-crimson-2` | icons вҖ” a red |\n58: | Teal | `#047ab1` | `--color-teal` | icons вҖ” a teal |\n59: | Crimson 3 | `#d42d06` | `--color-crimson-3` | icons вҖ” a red |\n60: | Light Magenta | `#ffa8cd` | `--color-light-magenta` | icons вҖ” a light magenta |\n61: | Voltage 3 | `#00d64f` | `--color-voltage-3` | icons вҖ” a green |\n62: | Crimson 4 | `#ff0033` | `--color-crimson-4` | icons вҖ” a red |\n63: | Voltage 4 | `#009f41` | `--color-voltage-4` | icons вҖ” a green |\n64: | Azure 16 | `#008cd5` | `--color-azure-16` | icons вҖ” a blue |\n65: | Citron | `#ffd100` | `--color-citron` | icons вҖ” a yellow |\n66: | Voltage 5 | `#0aad0a` | `--color-voltage-5` | icons вҖ” a green |\n67: | Magenta 2 | `#f363f3` | `--color-magenta-2` | gradients вҖ” a magenta |\n68: | Indigo 4 | `#7232f1` | `--color-indigo-4` | gradients вҖ” a indigo |\n69: | Magenta 3 | `#fb76fa` | `--color-magenta-3` | gradients вҖ” a magenta |\n70: | Azure 17 | `#486ffd` | `--color-azure-17` | gradients вҖ” a blue |\n71: | Light Indigo | `#dac0ff` | `--color-light-indigo` | gradients вҖ” a light indigo |\n72: | Light Magenta 2 | `#ff90b9` | `--color-light-magenta-2` | gradients вҖ” a light magenta |\n73: | Light Ember 3 | `#ffd79b` | `--color-light-ember-3` | gradients вҖ” a light orange |\n74: | Azure 18 | `#0071c1` | `--color-azure-18` | gradients вҖ” a blue |\n75: | Azure 19 | `#60a8e2` | `--color-azure-19` | gradients вҖ” a blue |\n76: | Ember 5 | `#ffb451` | `--color-ember-5` | gradients вҖ” a orange |\n77: | Ember 6 | `#ffa577` | `--color-ember-6` | gradients вҖ” a orange |\n78: | Light Crimson | `#ff90a1` | `--color-light-crimson` | gradients вҖ” a light red |\n79: | Light Indigo 2 | `#ddadff` | `--color-light-indigo-2` | gradients вҖ” a light indigo |\n80: | Light Indigo 3 | `#ecd8ff` | `--color-light-indigo-3` | gradients вҖ” a light indigo |\n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 606. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Stripe вҖ” Style Reference\n> Indigo-violet rationed against a white field вҖ” borders carry the structure, one saturated blue carries the brand.\n\n**Theme:** light\n\nThe canvas is pure Snow (`#ffffff`), and the system is built almost entirely from borders rather than fills вҖ” Ink (`#000000`) and a deep navy family draw nearly every line, frame, and divider on the page. A single saturated blue-violet, Azure (`#533afd`), is the brand signal: it owns link text, the primary CTA fill, and brand border accents, and almost nothing else competes with it. Body and UI text run in slate-blue tones (`#50617a`, `#64748d`) and deep navy (`#061b31`) rather than flat black, keeping the page tonal rather than high-contrast. Type is set in sohne-var across a wide variable range, with hierarchy carried by scale вҖ” a 56px display against a 16px body вҖ” and tightening letter-spacing as size grows. Depth is real but quiet: three shadow tokens, two of them tinted with the brand's own navy, give cards a soft chromatic lift instead of a hard drop shadow. Layout caps at 1266px on a spacious 4px-based rhythm, with section gaps stepping from 48px to 96px.\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n\n| Name | Value | Token | Role |\n|------|-------|-------|------|\n| Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a near-black |\n| Azure | `#533afd` | `--color-azure` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 2 | `#50617a` | `--color-azure-2` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n| Deep Azure | `#061b31` | `--color-deep-azure` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a deep blue |\n| Snow | `#ffffff` | `--color-snow` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a near-white |\n| Azure 3 | `#64748d` | `--color-azure-3` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 4 | `#0000ee` | `--color-azure-4` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 5 | `#3c4f69` | `--color-azure-5` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a blue |\n| Deep Azure 2 | `#273951` | `--color-deep-azure-2` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a deep blue |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/stripe/DESIGN.md","text":"# Stripe вҖ” Style Reference\n> Indigo-violet rationed against a white field вҖ” borders carry the structure, one saturated blue carries the brand.\n\n**Theme:** light\n\nThe canvas is pure Snow (`#ffffff`), and the system is built almost entirely from borders rather than fills вҖ” Ink (`#000000`) and a deep navy family draw nearly every line, frame, and divider on the page. A single saturated blue-violet, Azure (`#533afd`), is the brand signal: it owns link text, the primary CTA fill, and brand border accents, and almost nothing else competes with it. Body and UI text run in slate-blue tones (`#50617a`, `#64748d`) and deep navy (`#061b31`) rather than flat black, keeping the page tonal rather than high-contrast. Type is set in sohne-var across a wide variable range, with hierarchy carried by scale вҖ” a 56px display against a 16px body вҖ” and tightening letter-spacing as size grows. Depth is real but quiet: three shadow tokens, two of them tinted with the brand's own navy, give cards a soft chromatic lift instead of a hard drop shadow. Layout caps at 1266px on a spacious 4px-based rhythm, with section gaps stepping from 48px to 96px.\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n\n| Name | Value | Token | Role |\n|------|-------|-------|------|\n| Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a near-black |\n| Azure | `#533afd` | `--color-azure` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 2 | `#50617a` | `--color-azure-2` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n| Deep Azure | `#061b31` | `--color-deep-azure` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a deep blue |\n| Snow | `#ffffff` | `--color-snow` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a near-white |\n| Azure 3 | `#64748d` | `--color-azure-3` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 4 | `#0000ee` | `--color-azure-4` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 5 | `#3c4f69` | `--color-azure-5` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a blue |\n| Deep Azure 2 | `#273951` | `--color-deep-azure-2` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a deep blue |\n| Light Azure | `#e5edf5` | `--color-light-azure` | borders, backgrounds, gradients вҖ” a light blue |\n| Ember | `#ff6118` | `--color-ember` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a orange |\n| Deep Azure 3 | `#1a2c44` | `--color-deep-azure-3` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a deep blue |\n| Azure 6 | `#7389ff` | `--color-azure-6` | borders, text, gradients вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 7 | `#7d8ba4` | `--color-azure-7` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n| Light Azure 2 | `#b9b9f9` | `--color-light-azure-2` | borders вҖ” a light blue |\n| Light Azure 3 | `#d6d9fc` | `--color-light-azure-3` | borders, gradients вҖ” a light blue |\n| Azure 8 | `#839bc8` | `--color-azure-8` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 9 | `#7f7dfc` | `--color-azure-9` | borders, text, gradients вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 10 | `#a3b5d6` | `--color-azure-10` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n| Ink 2 | `#101010` | `--color-ink-2` | borders, text вҖ” a near-black |\n| Light Azure 4 | `#e2e4ff` | `--color-light-azure-4` | borders, backgrounds, gradients вҖ” a light blue |\n| Voltage | `#81b81a` | `--color-voltage` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a green |\n| Azure 11 | `#000eff` | `--color-azure-11` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 12 | `#2d2564` | `--color-azure-12` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n| Magenta | `#f44bcc` | `--color-magenta` | gradients вҖ” a magenta |\n| Deep Azure 4 | `#182659` | `--color-deep-azure-4` | borders, gradients вҖ” a deep blue |\n| Indigo | `#da4bfe` | `--color-indigo` | gradients вҖ” a indigo |\n| Obsidian | `#171717` | `--color-obsidian` | icons вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Light Ember | `#ffe0d1` | `--color-light-ember` | backgrounds вҖ” a light orange |\n| Azure 13 | `#32325d` | `--color-azure-13` | decorative use вҖ” a blue |\n| Light Azure 5 | `#d4dee9` | `--color-light-azure-5` | borders, icons вҖ” a light blue |\n| Deep Azure 5 | `#031323` | `--color-deep-azure-5` | backgrounds, icons вҖ” a deep blue |\n| Ember 2 | `#ffcf5e` | `--color-ember-2` | gradients вҖ” a orange |\n| Indigo 2 | `#4304ea` | `--color-indigo-2` | gradients вҖ” a indigo |\n| Light Azure 6 | `#b4d8ff` | `--color-light-azure-6` | gradients вҖ” a light blue |\n| Crimson | `#ff8c6c` | `--color-crimson` | gradients вҖ” a red |\n| Ember 3 | `#fbbc04` | `--color-ember-3` | icons вҖ” a orange |\n| Light Ember 2 | `#faf1e5` | `--color-light-ember-2` | icons, gradients вҖ” a light orange |\n| Indigo 3 | `#c489ff` | `--color-indigo-3` | gradients вҖ” a indigo |\n| Ember 4 | `#ffc977` | `--color-ember-4` | gradients вҖ” a orange |\n| Azure 14 | `#715cff` | `--color-azure-14` | gradients вҖ” a blue |\n| Voltage 2 | `#00d66f` | `--color-voltage-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a green |\n| Deep Teal | `#0b3b45` | `--color-deep-teal` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep teal |\n| Azure 15 | `#4285f4` | `--color-azure-15` | icons вҖ” a blue |\n| Sage | `#34a853` | `--color-sage` | icons вҖ” a green-gray |\n| Crimson 2 | `#ea4335` | `--color-crimson-2` | icons вҖ” a red |\n| Teal | `#047ab1` | `--color-teal` | icons вҖ” a teal |\n| Crimson 3 | `#d42d06` | `--color-crimson-3` | icons вҖ” a red |\n| Light Magenta | `#ffa8cd` | `--color-light-magenta` | icons вҖ” a light magenta |\n| Voltage 3 | `#00d64f` | `--color-voltage-3` | icons вҖ” a green |\n| Crimson 4 | `#ff0033` | `--color-crimson-4` | icons вҖ” a red |\n| Voltage 4 | `#009f41` | `--color-voltage-4` | icons вҖ” a green |\n| Azure 16 | `#008cd5` | `--color-azure-16` | icons вҖ” a blue |\n| Citron | `#ffd100` | `--color-citron` | icons вҖ” a yellow |\n| Voltage 5 | `#0aad0a` | `--color-voltage-5` | icons вҖ” a green |\n| Magenta 2 | `#f363f3` | `--color-magenta-2` | gradients вҖ” a magenta |\n| Indigo 4 | `#7232f1` | `--color-indigo-4` | gradients вҖ” a indigo |\n| Magenta 3 | `#fb76fa` | `--color-magenta-3` | gradients вҖ” a magenta |\n| Azure 17 | `#486ffd` | `--color-azure-17` | gradients вҖ” a blue |\n| Light Indigo | `#dac0ff` | `--color-light-indigo` | gradients вҖ” a light indigo |\n| Light Magenta 2 | `#ff90b9` | `--color-light-magenta-2` | gradients вҖ” a light magenta |\n| Light Ember 3 | `#ffd79b` | `--color-light-ember-3` | gradients вҖ” a light orange |\n| Azure 18 | `#0071c1` | `--color-azure-18` | gradients вҖ” a blue |\n| Azure 19 | `#60a8e2` | `--color-azure-19` | gradients вҖ” a blue |\n| Ember 5 | `#ffb451` | `--color-ember-5` | gradients вҖ” a orange |\n| Ember 6 | `#ffa577` | `--color-ember-6` | gradients вҖ” a orange |\n| Light Crimson | `#ff90a1` | `--color-light-crimson` | gradients вҖ” a light red |\n| Light Indigo 2 | `#ddadff` | `--color-light-indigo-2` | gradients вҖ” a light indigo |\n| Light Indigo 3 | `#ecd8ff` | `--color-light-indigo-3` | gradients вҖ” a light indigo |","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":606,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/stripe/DESIGN.md","time":{"start":1782532433593,"end":1782532433614}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f9f392428e18d6d016a3f495163d88194a9c768c7b2d33222"}},"id":"prt_f073666b7001Kx9vyN9kKcj8cl","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","messageID":"msg_f073583cf001yFIFOrufYdGerR"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532433618,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vF3356OhlDN6Nyh5Is4jpXCf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/vercel/DESIGN.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/vercel/DESIGN.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Vercel вҖ” Style Reference\n2: > Developer infrastructure made invisible вҖ” an achromatic field where a hairline `#ebebeb` box-shadow does the work a border would.\n3: \n4: **Theme:** light\n5: \n6: The canvas is Snow (`#ffffff`), and Obsidian (`#171717`) carries text, borders, and backgrounds as a deep near-black that stops short of pure `#000000`. Geist and Geist Mono run the page: display type reaches 48px at -2.88px tracking against a 14px UI body, so hierarchy is built from scale and compression, not from heavy weights вҖ” nothing exceeds weight 600. Colour is rationed hard вҖ” the field is neutral gray (Graphite, Slate, Steel) with Azure (`#0068d6`) reserved for badges and interactive accents, and a wide chromatic reserve (Magenta, Crimson, Teal, Voltage, Ember) that surfaces only in icons and decorative gradients, never as page chrome. Buttons and pills round to a 9999px full-pill, while cards and inputs sit at a 6px corner. Depth is real but quiet: 14 shadow tokens, most of them a 1px `#ebebeb` ring standing in for a border, with whitespace at 96px-plus section gaps doing the rest. Layout runs full-width at 100% max, collapsing through a dominant `960px` breakpoint.\n7: \n8: ## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n9: \n10: | Name | Value | Token | Role |\n11: |------|-------|-------|------|\n12: | Obsidian | `#171717` | `--color-obsidian` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n13: | Graphite | `#4d4d4d` | `--color-graphite` | borders, text вҖ” a dark gray |\n14: | Linen | `#ebebeb` | `--color-linen` | borders, gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a soft off-white |\n15: | Slate | `#666666` | `--color-slate` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a mid gray |\n16: | Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a near-black |\n17: | Slate 2 | `#808080` | `--color-slate-2` | borders, text вҖ” a mid gray |\n18: | Snow | `#ffffff` | `--color-snow` | borders, backgrounds, text вҖ” a near-white |\n19: | Steel | `#8f8f8f` | `--color-steel` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a light gray |\n20: | Steel 2 | `#a8a8a8` | `--color-steel-2` | borders, text вҖ” a light gray |\n21: | Azure | `#0068d6` | `--color-azure` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a blue |\n22: | Magenta | `#bd2864` | `--color-magenta` | borders, text вҖ” a magenta |\n23: | Azure 2 | `#52aeff` | `--color-azure-2` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a blue |\n24: | Crimson | `#e5484d` | `--color-crimson` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a red |\n25: | Teal | `#45dec5` | `--color-teal` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a teal |\n26: | Ember | `#ffb224` | `--color-ember` | borders, text вҖ” a orange |\n27: | Sage | `#297a3a` | `--color-sage` | borders, text вҖ” a green-gray |\n28: | Light Teal | `#d4eef7` | `--color-light-teal` | gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a light teal |\n29: | Light Voltage | `#c7f5e2` | `--color-light-voltage` | gradients вҖ” a light green |\n30: | Light Ember | `#f7ead4` | `--color-light-ember` | gradients вҖ” a light orange |\n31: | Azure 3 | `#006bff` | `--color-azure-3` | borders вҖ” a blue |\n32: | Indigo | `#7820bc` | `--color-indigo` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a indigo |\n33: | Steel 3 | `#999999` | `--color-steel-3` | text, borders вҖ” a light gray |\n34: | Light Azure | `#ebf5ff` | `--color-light-azure` | backgrounds вҖ” a light blue |\n35: | Ember 2 | `#ff990a` | `--color-ember-2` | backgrounds, icons вҖ” a orange |\n36: | Crimson 2 | `#ff0000` | `--color-crimson-2` | icons вҖ” a red |\n37: | Voltage | `#00dc82` | `--color-voltage` | icons вҖ” a green |\n38: | Crimson 3 | `#ff3e00` | `--color-crimson-3` | icons вҖ” a red |\n39: | Sage 2 | `#398e4a` | `--color-sage-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a green-gray |\n40: | Sage 3 | `#45a557` | `--color-sage-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a green-gray |\n41: | Indigo 2 | `#bf89ec` | `--color-indigo-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a indigo |\n42: | Magenta 2 | `#ea3e83` | `--color-magenta-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a magenta |\n43: | Teal 2 | `#067a6e` | `--color-teal-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a teal |\n44: | Voltage 2 | `#6cda75` | `--color-voltage-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a green |\n45: | Linen 2 | `#d9d9d9` | `--color-linen-2` | icons вҖ” a soft off-white |\n46: | Azure 4 | `#0078d4` | `--color-azure-4` | icons вҖ” a blue |\n47: | Crimson 4 | `#e24329` | `--color-crimson-4` | icons вҖ” a red |\n48: | Ember 3 | `#fc6d26` | `--color-ember-3` | icons вҖ” a orange |\n49: | Azure 5 | `#2684ff` | `--color-azure-5` | icons вҖ” a blue |\n50: | Teal 3 | `#149eca` | `--color-teal-3` | icons вҖ” a teal |\n51: | Citron | `#eec32d` | `--color-citron` | gradients вҖ” a yellow |\n52: | Azure 6 | `#709ab9` | `--color-azure-6` | gradients вҖ” a blue |\n53: | Voltage 3 | `#4dffbf` | `--color-voltage-3` | gradients вҖ” a green |\n54: \n55: ## Tokens вҖ” Typography\n56: \n57: ### Geist вҖ” Primary UI and display typeface, geometric sans-serif В· `--font-geist`\n58: - **Substitute:** Inter, system-ui, sans-serif\n59: - **Weights:** 400, 500, 600\n60: - **Sizes:** 12px, 13px, 14px, 16px, 18px, 20px, 24px, 32px, 40px, 48px\n61: - **Line height:** 12px through 56px, with `normal` on the smallest UI sizes\n62: - **Letter spacing:** normal up to 20px; tightening to -0.96px at 24px, -1.28px at 32px, -2.4px at 40px, and -2.88px at 48px\n63: - **Role:** Carries every UI surface вҖ” body copy, navigation, buttons, badges, and the full heading-to-display ramp. The negative tracking is reserved for the large end of the scale, so headlines read as compressed while body stays at normal spacing.\n64: \n65: ### Geist Mono вҖ” Code, technical labels, and inline command text В· `--font-geist-mono`\n66: - **Substitute:** ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, monospace\n67: - **Weights:** 400, 500\n68: - **Sizes:** 13px (the captured code/`pre` level)\n69: - **Role:** The monospaced counterpart used where command snippets and code samples appear, set at 13px with a 20px line-height for dense technical lines.\n70: \n71: ### Type Scale\n72: \n73: | Role | Size | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Token |\n74: |------|------|-------------|----------------|-------|\n75: | caption | 12px | 16px | normal | `--text-caption` |\n76: | body-sm | 13px | 20px | normal | `--text-body-sm` |\n77: | body | 14px | 20px | normal | `--text-body` |\n78: | body-lg | 16px | 24px | normal | `--text-body-lg` |\n79: | subheading | 18px | 27.36px | normal | `--text-subheading` |\n80: | heading-sm | 20px | 36px | normal | `--text-heading-sm` |\n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 540. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Vercel вҖ” Style Reference\n> Developer infrastructure made invisible вҖ” an achromatic field where a hairline `#ebebeb` box-shadow does the work a border would.\n\n**Theme:** light\n\nThe canvas is Snow (`#ffffff`), and Obsidian (`#171717`) carries text, borders, and backgrounds as a deep near-black that stops short of pure `#000000`. Geist and Geist Mono run the page: display type reaches 48px at -2.88px tracking against a 14px UI body, so hierarchy is built from scale and compression, not from heavy weights вҖ” nothing exceeds weight 600. Colour is rationed hard вҖ” the field is neutral gray (Graphite, Slate, Steel) with Azure (`#0068d6`) reserved for badges and interactive accents, and a wide chromatic reserve (Magenta, Crimson, Teal, Voltage, Ember) that surfaces only in icons and decorative gradients, never as page chrome. Buttons and pills round to a 9999px full-pill, while cards and inputs sit at a 6px corner. Depth is real but quiet: 14 shadow tokens, most of them a 1px `#ebebeb` ring standing in for a border, with whitespace at 96px-plus section gaps doing the rest. Layout runs full-width at 100% max, collapsing through a dominant `960px` breakpoint.\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n\n| Name | Value | Token | Role |\n|------|-------|-------|------|\n| Obsidian | `#171717` | `--color-obsidian` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Graphite | `#4d4d4d` | `--color-graphite` | borders, text вҖ” a dark gray |\n| Linen | `#ebebeb` | `--color-linen` | borders, gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a soft off-white |\n| Slate | `#666666` | `--color-slate` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a mid gray |\n| Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a near-black |\n| Slate 2 | `#808080` | `--color-slate-2` | borders, text вҖ” a mid gray |\n| Snow | `#ffffff` | `--color-snow` | borders, backgrounds, text вҖ” a near-white |\n| Steel | `#8f8f8f` | `--color-steel` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a light gray |\n| Steel 2 | `#a8a8a8` | `--color-steel-2` | borders, text вҖ” a light gray |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/vercel/DESIGN.md","text":"# Vercel вҖ” Style Reference\n> Developer infrastructure made invisible вҖ” an achromatic field where a hairline `#ebebeb` box-shadow does the work a border would.\n\n**Theme:** light\n\nThe canvas is Snow (`#ffffff`), and Obsidian (`#171717`) carries text, borders, and backgrounds as a deep near-black that stops short of pure `#000000`. Geist and Geist Mono run the page: display type reaches 48px at -2.88px tracking against a 14px UI body, so hierarchy is built from scale and compression, not from heavy weights вҖ” nothing exceeds weight 600. Colour is rationed hard вҖ” the field is neutral gray (Graphite, Slate, Steel) with Azure (`#0068d6`) reserved for badges and interactive accents, and a wide chromatic reserve (Magenta, Crimson, Teal, Voltage, Ember) that surfaces only in icons and decorative gradients, never as page chrome. Buttons and pills round to a 9999px full-pill, while cards and inputs sit at a 6px corner. Depth is real but quiet: 14 shadow tokens, most of them a 1px `#ebebeb` ring standing in for a border, with whitespace at 96px-plus section gaps doing the rest. Layout runs full-width at 100% max, collapsing through a dominant `960px` breakpoint.\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n\n| Name | Value | Token | Role |\n|------|-------|-------|------|\n| Obsidian | `#171717` | `--color-obsidian` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Graphite | `#4d4d4d` | `--color-graphite` | borders, text вҖ” a dark gray |\n| Linen | `#ebebeb` | `--color-linen` | borders, gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a soft off-white |\n| Slate | `#666666` | `--color-slate` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a mid gray |\n| Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a near-black |\n| Slate 2 | `#808080` | `--color-slate-2` | borders, text вҖ” a mid gray |\n| Snow | `#ffffff` | `--color-snow` | borders, backgrounds, text вҖ” a near-white |\n| Steel | `#8f8f8f` | `--color-steel` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a light gray |\n| Steel 2 | `#a8a8a8` | `--color-steel-2` | borders, text вҖ” a light gray |\n| Azure | `#0068d6` | `--color-azure` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a blue |\n| Magenta | `#bd2864` | `--color-magenta` | borders, text вҖ” a magenta |\n| Azure 2 | `#52aeff` | `--color-azure-2` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a blue |\n| Crimson | `#e5484d` | `--color-crimson` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a red |\n| Teal | `#45dec5` | `--color-teal` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a teal |\n| Ember | `#ffb224` | `--color-ember` | borders, text вҖ” a orange |\n| Sage | `#297a3a` | `--color-sage` | borders, text вҖ” a green-gray |\n| Light Teal | `#d4eef7` | `--color-light-teal` | gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a light teal |\n| Light Voltage | `#c7f5e2` | `--color-light-voltage` | gradients вҖ” a light green |\n| Light Ember | `#f7ead4` | `--color-light-ember` | gradients вҖ” a light orange |\n| Azure 3 | `#006bff` | `--color-azure-3` | borders вҖ” a blue |\n| Indigo | `#7820bc` | `--color-indigo` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a indigo |\n| Steel 3 | `#999999` | `--color-steel-3` | text, borders вҖ” a light gray |\n| Light Azure | `#ebf5ff` | `--color-light-azure` | backgrounds вҖ” a light blue |\n| Ember 2 | `#ff990a` | `--color-ember-2` | backgrounds, icons вҖ” a orange |\n| Crimson 2 | `#ff0000` | `--color-crimson-2` | icons вҖ” a red |\n| Voltage | `#00dc82` | `--color-voltage` | icons вҖ” a green |\n| Crimson 3 | `#ff3e00` | `--color-crimson-3` | icons вҖ” a red |\n| Sage 2 | `#398e4a` | `--color-sage-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a green-gray |\n| Sage 3 | `#45a557` | `--color-sage-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a green-gray |\n| Indigo 2 | `#bf89ec` | `--color-indigo-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a indigo |\n| Magenta 2 | `#ea3e83` | `--color-magenta-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a magenta |\n| Teal 2 | `#067a6e` | `--color-teal-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a teal |\n| Voltage 2 | `#6cda75` | `--color-voltage-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a green |\n| Linen 2 | `#d9d9d9` | `--color-linen-2` | icons вҖ” a soft off-white |\n| Azure 4 | `#0078d4` | `--color-azure-4` | icons вҖ” a blue |\n| Crimson 4 | `#e24329` | `--color-crimson-4` | icons вҖ” a red |\n| Ember 3 | `#fc6d26` | `--color-ember-3` | icons вҖ” a orange |\n| Azure 5 | `#2684ff` | `--color-azure-5` | icons вҖ” a blue |\n| Teal 3 | `#149eca` | `--color-teal-3` | icons вҖ” a teal |\n| Citron | `#eec32d` | `--color-citron` | gradients вҖ” a yellow |\n| Azure 6 | `#709ab9` | `--color-azure-6` | gradients вҖ” a blue |\n| Voltage 3 | `#4dffbf` | `--color-voltage-3` | gradients вҖ” a green |\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Typography\n\n### Geist вҖ” Primary UI and display typeface, geometric sans-serif В· `--font-geist`\n- **Substitute:** Inter, system-ui, sans-serif\n- **Weights:** 400, 500, 600\n- **Sizes:** 12px, 13px, 14px, 16px, 18px, 20px, 24px, 32px, 40px, 48px\n- **Line height:** 12px through 56px, with `normal` on the smallest UI sizes\n- **Letter spacing:** normal up to 20px; tightening to -0.96px at 24px, -1.28px at 32px, -2.4px at 40px, and -2.88px at 48px\n- **Role:** Carries every UI surface вҖ” body copy, navigation, buttons, badges, and the full heading-to-display ramp. The negative tracking is reserved for the large end of the scale, so headlines read as compressed while body stays at normal spacing.\n\n### Geist Mono вҖ” Code, technical labels, and inline command text В· `--font-geist-mono`\n- **Substitute:** ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, monospace\n- **Weights:** 400, 500\n- **Sizes:** 13px (the captured code/`pre` level)\n- **Role:** The monospaced counterpart used where command snippets and code samples appear, set at 13px with a 20px line-height for dense technical lines.\n\n### Type Scale\n\n| Role | Size | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Token |\n|------|------|-------------|----------------|-------|\n| caption | 12px | 16px | normal | `--text-caption` |\n| body-sm | 13px | 20px | normal | `--text-body-sm` |\n| body | 14px | 20px | normal | `--text-body` |\n| body-lg | 16px | 24px | normal | `--text-body-lg` |\n| subheading | 18px | 27.36px | normal | `--text-subheading` |\n| heading-sm | 20px | 36px | normal | `--text-heading-sm` |","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":540,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/vercel/DESIGN.md","time":{"start":1782532433597,"end":1782532433617}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f9f392428e18d6d016a3f495163e08194be0f3214ca7ecf9b"}},"id":"prt_f073666bc00125WieZG6HjgMpW","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","messageID":"msg_f073583cf001yFIFOrufYdGerR"}}
