write-prompt.ts` вҶ’ author prose вҶ’ `validate.ts`. The value-bearing sections (Colors, Spacing & Shapes, Surfaces, Quick Start) are pasted verbatim from the deterministic formatter.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/supabase/DESIGN.md:\n  Line 1: # Supabase вҖ” Style Reference\n\n  Line 2: > Postgres infrastructure rendered in near-black вҖ” one Voltage green threading an achromatic developer canvas.\n\n  Line 4: **Theme:** dark\n\n  Line 229: - **Vercel** вҖ” Near-black developer-tool canvas, restrained gray ramp, one accent, and large geometric display type.\n\n  Line 230: - **Railway** вҖ” Dark infrastructure aesthetic with a green-family accent on a gray ramp and monospace numerics for plan and usage figures.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/linear/DESIGN.md:\n  Line 1: # Linear вҖ” Style Reference\n\n  Line 4: **Theme:** dark\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/supabase/writing-notes.md:\n  Line 1: # Writing Notes: Supabase DESIGN.md (v3)\n\n  Line 3: - This is a v3 **Style Reference**, regenerated from the existing `tokens.json` with no re-crawl. Value-bearing sections (Tokens вҖ” Colors, Spacing & Shapes, Surfaces, Quick Start) are pasted verbatim from `build-write-prompt.ts`; only prose was authored.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/vercel/DESIGN.md:\n  Line 1: # Vercel вҖ” Style Reference\n\n  Line 2: > Developer infrastructure made invisible вҖ” an achromatic field where a hairline `#ebebeb` box-shadow does the work a border would.\n\n  Line 4: **Theme:** light\n","metadata":{"matches":20,"truncated":false},"title":"^# |Theme:|Style Reference|SaaS|minimal|developer|infrastructure","time":{"start":1782532433609,"end":1782532433628}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f9f392428e18d6d016a3f4951640c8194973b2b852d34efe5"}},"id":"prt_f073666c7001R7iXTy36Yl1Tv1","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","messageID":"msg_f073583cf001yFIFOrufYdGerR"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532433632,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4huAKB01MYXM5X7w7SFGmYav","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/supabase/DESIGN.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/supabase/DESIGN.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Supabase вҖ” Style Reference\n2: > Postgres infrastructure rendered in near-black вҖ” one Voltage green threading an achromatic developer canvas.\n3: \n4: **Theme:** dark\n5: \n6: The canvas is a near-black field вҖ” `#171717` cards and `#0f0f0f` footers layered against true `#000000`, with Snow (`#fafafa`) carrying nearly all text at 17:1 contrast or higher. Colour is rationed hard: a single Voltage green (`#3ecf8e`) is the only chromatic signal across an otherwise achromatic ramp of grays, from Slate (`#898989`) body text down through Graphite (`#4d4d4d`) and Obsidian (`#2e2e2e`) borders. Two typefaces split the work вҖ” Circular sets every heading and body run from 12px to a 72px hero, while Source Code Pro is reserved for numerics and uppercase tier labels (`$0`, `FREE`, `PRO`). Spacing rides a strict 4px base unit through a 14-step scale, and the page runs full-bleed at 100% width. Pill radii (`9999px`) and 6px controls do the shaping; depth is mostly carried by tonal contrast rather than shadow.\n7: \n8: ## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n9: \n10: | Name | Value | Token | Role |\n11: |------|-------|-------|------|\n12: | Obsidian | `#2e2e2e` | `--color-obsidian` | borders, gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n13: | Snow | `#fafafa` | `--color-snow` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a near-white |\n14: | Slate | `#898989` | `--color-slate` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a mid gray |\n15: | Graphite | `#4d4d4d` | `--color-graphite` | text, borders вҖ” a dark gray |\n16: | Steel | `#b4b4b4` | `--color-steel` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a light gray |\n17: | Graphite 2 | `#393939` | `--color-graphite-2` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a dark gray |\n18: | Obsidian 2 | `#171717` | `--color-obsidian-2` | backgrounds, text, gradients вҖ” a deep near-black |\n19: | Voltage | `#3ecf8e` | `--color-voltage` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a green |\n20: | Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |\n21: | Obsidian 3 | `#242424` | `--color-obsidian-3` | borders, backgrounds, text вҖ” a deep near-black |\n22: | Deep Voltage | `#006239` | `--color-deep-voltage` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep green |\n23: | Ink 2 | `#0f0f0f` | `--color-ink-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |\n24: | Voltage 2 | `#00c573` | `--color-voltage-2` | text, borders вҖ” a green |\n25: | Voltage 3 | `#85e0ba` | `--color-voltage-3` | text, borders вҖ” a green |\n26: | Ember | `#db8e00` | `--color-ember` | borders вҖ” a orange |\n27: | Deep Voltage 2 | `#002918` | `--color-deep-voltage-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep green |\n28: | Light Azure | `#93c5fd` | `--color-light-azure` | decorative use вҖ” a light blue |\n29: \n30: ## Tokens вҖ” Typography\n31: \n32: Two families divide cleanly: Circular owns prose and headings, Source Code Pro owns figures and tier labels. Both run at weight 400 almost everywhere вҖ” hierarchy comes from size, not weight.\n33: \n34: ### Circular вҖ” Primary brand typeface, geometric sans-serif. Headings, body, navigation, and buttons. В· `--font-circular`\n35: - **Substitute:** Inter, system sans-serif\n36: - **Weights:** 400, 500\n37: - **Sizes:** 12px, 13px, 14px, 16px, 18px, 20px, 24px, 30px, 36px, 72px\n38: - **Line height:** 16px, 19.5px, 20px, 24px, 28px, 32px, 36px, 40px, 72px\n39: - **Letter spacing:** normal, except -0.16px at the 24px body-paragraph level\n40: - **Role:** Carries the 72px hero (\"Build in a weekend / Scale to millions\"), every heading, all body copy, and the 14px / weight 500 navigation and button labels.\n41: \n42: ### Source Code Pro вҖ” Monospace numerics and uppercase tier labels. В· `--font-source-code-pro`\n43: - **Substitute:** Fira Code, monospace\n44: - **Weights:** 400, 500, 700\n45: - **Sizes:** 11px, 12px, 18px, 20px, 24px, 36px, 48px\n46: - **Letter spacing:** normal, except 0.66px at the 11px uppercase micro-label\n47: - **Role:** Reserved for pricing figures (`$0`, `$25`, `$599`) and uppercase plan/section labels (`FREE`, `PRO`, `TEAM`, `CUSTOMER STORIES`). Several levels carry text-transform uppercase; the 11px / weight 500 / 0.66px-tracked micro-label (\"Micro\") is the smallest type in the system.\n48: \n49: ### Type Scale\n50: \n51: | Role | Size | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Token |\n52: |------|------|-------------|----------------|-------|\n53: | caption | 11px | 12.1px | 0.66px | `--text-caption` |\n54: | body-sm | 12px | 16px | normal | `--text-body-sm` |\n55: | body | 13px | 19.5px | normal | `--text-body` |\n56: | body-lg | 14px | 20px | normal | `--text-body-lg` |\n57: | subheading | 16px | 24px | normal | `--text-subheading` |\n58: | heading-sm | 18px | 28px | normal | `--text-heading-sm` |\n59: | heading | 20px | 28px | normal | `--text-heading` |\n60: | heading-lg | 24px | 32px | -0.16px | `--text-heading-lg` |\n61: | title | 30px | 36px | normal | `--text-title` |\n62: | title-lg | 36px | 40px | normal | `--text-title-lg` |\n63: | display | 48px | 48px | normal | `--text-display` |\n64: | hero | 72px | 72px | normal | `--text-hero` |\n65: \n66: The caption role (11px / 0.66px tracking, uppercase) and the display role (48px, used for the largest pricing figures) are both Source Code Pro; everything from body through hero is Circular. The -0.16px tracking appears only at the 24px body-paragraph level вҖ” every other level runs at normal tracking.\n67: \n68: ## Tokens вҖ” Spacing & Shapes\n69: \n70: **Base unit:** 4px\n71: **Density:** spacious\n72: \n73: ### Spacing Scale\n74: \n75: | Name | Value | Token |\n76: |------|-------|-------|\n77: | 4 | 4px | `--spacing-4` |\n78: | 8 | 8px | `--spacing-8` |\n79: | 12 | 12px | `--spacing-12` |\n80: | 16 | 16px | `--spacing-16` |\n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 417. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Supabase вҖ” Style Reference\n> Postgres infrastructure rendered in near-black вҖ” one Voltage green threading an achromatic developer canvas.\n\n**Theme:** dark\n\nThe canvas is a near-black field вҖ” `#171717` cards and `#0f0f0f` footers layered against true `#000000`, with Snow (`#fafafa`) carrying nearly all text at 17:1 contrast or higher. Colour is rationed hard: a single Voltage green (`#3ecf8e`) is the only chromatic signal across an otherwise achromatic ramp of grays, from Slate (`#898989`) body text down through Graphite (`#4d4d4d`) and Obsidian (`#2e2e2e`) borders. Two typefaces split the work вҖ” Circular sets every heading and body run from 12px to a 72px hero, while Source Code Pro is reserved for numerics and uppercase tier labels (`$0`, `FREE`, `PRO`). Spacing rides a strict 4px base unit through a 14-step scale, and the page runs full-bleed at 100% width. Pill radii (`9999px`) and 6px controls do the shaping; depth is mostly carried by tonal contrast rather than shadow.\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n\n| Name | Value | Token | Role |\n|------|-------|-------|------|\n| Obsidian | `#2e2e2e` | `--color-obsidian` | borders, gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Snow | `#fafafa` | `--color-snow` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a near-white |\n| Slate | `#898989` | `--color-slate` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a mid gray |\n| Graphite | `#4d4d4d` | `--color-graphite` | text, borders вҖ” a dark gray |\n| Steel | `#b4b4b4` | `--color-steel` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a light gray |\n| Graphite 2 | `#393939` | `--color-graphite-2` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a dark gray |\n| Obsidian 2 | `#171717` | `--color-obsidian-2` | backgrounds, text, gradients вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Voltage | `#3ecf8e` | `--color-voltage` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a green |\n| Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/supabase/DESIGN.md","text":"# Supabase вҖ” Style Reference\n> Postgres infrastructure rendered in near-black вҖ” one Voltage green threading an achromatic developer canvas.\n\n**Theme:** dark\n\nThe canvas is a near-black field вҖ” `#171717` cards and `#0f0f0f` footers layered against true `#000000`, with Snow (`#fafafa`) carrying nearly all text at 17:1 contrast or higher. Colour is rationed hard: a single Voltage green (`#3ecf8e`) is the only chromatic signal across an otherwise achromatic ramp of grays, from Slate (`#898989`) body text down through Graphite (`#4d4d4d`) and Obsidian (`#2e2e2e`) borders. Two typefaces split the work вҖ” Circular sets every heading and body run from 12px to a 72px hero, while Source Code Pro is reserved for numerics and uppercase tier labels (`$0`, `FREE`, `PRO`). Spacing rides a strict 4px base unit through a 14-step scale, and the page runs full-bleed at 100% width. Pill radii (`9999px`) and 6px controls do the shaping; depth is mostly carried by tonal contrast rather than shadow.\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n\n| Name | Value | Token | Role |\n|------|-------|-------|------|\n| Obsidian | `#2e2e2e` | `--color-obsidian` | borders, gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Snow | `#fafafa` | `--color-snow` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a near-white |\n| Slate | `#898989` | `--color-slate` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a mid gray |\n| Graphite | `#4d4d4d` | `--color-graphite` | text, borders вҖ” a dark gray |\n| Steel | `#b4b4b4` | `--color-steel` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a light gray |\n| Graphite 2 | `#393939` | `--color-graphite-2` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a dark gray |\n| Obsidian 2 | `#171717` | `--color-obsidian-2` | backgrounds, text, gradients вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Voltage | `#3ecf8e` | `--color-voltage` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a green |\n| Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |\n| Obsidian 3 | `#242424` | `--color-obsidian-3` | borders, backgrounds, text вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Deep Voltage | `#006239` | `--color-deep-voltage` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep green |\n| Ink 2 | `#0f0f0f` | `--color-ink-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |\n| Voltage 2 | `#00c573` | `--color-voltage-2` | text, borders вҖ” a green |\n| Voltage 3 | `#85e0ba` | `--color-voltage-3` | text, borders вҖ” a green |\n| Ember | `#db8e00` | `--color-ember` | borders вҖ” a orange |\n| Deep Voltage 2 | `#002918` | `--color-deep-voltage-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep green |\n| Light Azure | `#93c5fd` | `--color-light-azure` | decorative use вҖ” a light blue |\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Typography\n\nTwo families divide cleanly: Circular owns prose and headings, Source Code Pro owns figures and tier labels. Both run at weight 400 almost everywhere вҖ” hierarchy comes from size, not weight.\n\n### Circular вҖ” Primary brand typeface, geometric sans-serif. Headings, body, navigation, and buttons. В· `--font-circular`\n- **Substitute:** Inter, system sans-serif\n- **Weights:** 400, 500\n- **Sizes:** 12px, 13px, 14px, 16px, 18px, 20px, 24px, 30px, 36px, 72px\n- **Line height:** 16px, 19.5px, 20px, 24px, 28px, 32px, 36px, 40px, 72px\n- **Letter spacing:** normal, except -0.16px at the 24px body-paragraph level\n- **Role:** Carries the 72px hero (\"Build in a weekend / Scale to millions\"), every heading, all body copy, and the 14px / weight 500 navigation and button labels.\n\n### Source Code Pro вҖ” Monospace numerics and uppercase tier labels. В· `--font-source-code-pro`\n- **Substitute:** Fira Code, monospace\n- **Weights:** 400, 500, 700\n- **Sizes:** 11px, 12px, 18px, 20px, 24px, 36px, 48px\n- **Letter spacing:** normal, except 0.66px at the 11px uppercase micro-label\n- **Role:** Reserved for pricing figures (`$0`, `$25`, `$599`) and uppercase plan/section labels (`FREE`, `PRO`, `TEAM`, `CUSTOMER STORIES`). Several levels carry text-transform uppercase; the 11px / weight 500 / 0.66px-tracked micro-label (\"Micro\") is the smallest type in the system.\n\n### Type Scale\n\n| Role | Size | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Token |\n|------|------|-------------|----------------|-------|\n| caption | 11px | 12.1px | 0.66px | `--text-caption` |\n| body-sm | 12px | 16px | normal | `--text-body-sm` |\n| body | 13px | 19.5px | normal | `--text-body` |\n| body-lg | 14px | 20px | normal | `--text-body-lg` |\n| subheading | 16px | 24px | normal | `--text-subheading` |\n| heading-sm | 18px | 28px | normal | `--text-heading-sm` |\n| heading | 20px | 28px | normal | `--text-heading` |\n| heading-lg | 24px | 32px | -0.16px | `--text-heading-lg` |\n| title | 30px | 36px | normal | `--text-title` |\n| title-lg | 36px | 40px | normal | `--text-title-lg` |\n| display | 48px | 48px | normal | `--text-display` |\n| hero | 72px | 72px | normal | `--text-hero` |\n\nThe caption role (11px / 0.66px tracking, uppercase) and the display role (48px, used for the largest pricing figures) are both Source Code Pro; everything from body through hero is Circular. The -0.16px tracking appears only at the 24px body-paragraph level вҖ” every other level runs at normal tracking.\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Spacing & Shapes\n\n**Base unit:** 4px\n**Density:** spacious\n\n### Spacing Scale\n\n| Name | Value | Token |\n|------|-------|-------|\n| 4 | 4px | `--spacing-4` |\n| 8 | 8px | `--spacing-8` |\n| 12 | 12px | `--spacing-12` |\n| 16 | 16px | `--spacing-16` |","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":417,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/supabase/DESIGN.md","time":{"start":1782532433606,"end":1782532433631}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f9f392428e18d6d016a3f495164048194a3127c479b7b91ac"}},"id":"prt_f073666c400137rgyO0uofp5Qa","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","messageID":"msg_f073583cf001yFIFOrufYdGerR"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532433632,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_uK0de4yyM0i8fJhRHfdQsint","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/linear/DESIGN.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/linear/DESIGN.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Linear вҖ” Style Reference\n2: > A near-black product canvas where content surfaces through luminance, and a single indigo is the only thing allowed to glow.\n3: \n4: **Theme:** dark\n5: \n6: Linear builds on a near-black canvas (`#08090a`), against which Snow text (`#f7f8f8`) sits at 19.74:1 contrast вҖ” the dominant pairing across the entire surface. Inter Variable carries every word, ranging from a 10px caption to a 72px hero, with hierarchy driven by tracking that tightens as size grows (-0.15px at 10px down to -1.584px at the largest heading). Colour is rationed hard: most of the 43 tokens are achromatic grays stepping from Snow through Steel (`#8a8f98`) and Slate (`#62666d`) to the Ink near-blacks, and Azure 3 (`#5e6ad2`) is the one indigo reserved for the brand accent and badges. Surfaces are not painted in вҖ” interactive elements are built from near-transparent white overlays (`rgba(255,255,255,0.01)` to `0.05`) that only resolve into panels through hairline borders and a deep 16-token shadow stack. Layout runs edge to edge at 100% width with section spacing that swings from 48px up past 200px, framing each block as a self-contained slab. Berkeley Mono handles code, the one place the system leaves its sans-serif voice.\n7: \n8: ## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n9: \n10: | Name | Value | Token | Role |\n11: |------|-------|-------|------|\n12: | Snow | `#f7f8f8` | `--color-snow` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a near-white |\n13: | Slate | `#62666d` | `--color-slate` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a mid gray |\n14: | Light Azure | `#d0d6e0` | `--color-light-azure` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a light blue |\n15: | Steel | `#8a8f98` | `--color-steel` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a light gray |\n16: | Linen | `#e2e4e7` | `--color-linen` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a soft off-white |\n17: | Light Magenta | `#f79ce0` | `--color-light-magenta` | borders, text вҖ” a light magenta |\n18: | Obsidian | `#202122` | `--color-obsidian` | borders, gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n19: | Teal | `#55cdff` | `--color-teal` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a teal |\n20: | Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |\n21: | Ink 2 | `#08090a` | `--color-ink-2` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |\n22: | Ember | `#ffc47c` | `--color-ember` | borders, text вҖ” a orange |\n23: | Light Azure 2 | `#8fa4ff` | `--color-light-azure-2` | borders, text вҖ” a light blue |\n24: | Sage | `#89d196` | `--color-sage` | borders, text вҖ” a green-gray |\n25: | Voltage | `#00ff05` | `--color-voltage` | backgrounds вҖ” a green |\n26: | Graphite | `#383b3f` | `--color-graphite` | borders, backgrounds, icons вҖ” a dark gray |\n27: | Crimson | `#d6303d` | `--color-crimson` | text, borders вҖ” a red |\n28: | Voltage 2 | `#008d2c` | `--color-voltage-2` | text, borders вҖ” a green |\n29: | Crimson 2 | `#eb5757` | `--color-crimson-2` | borders, backgrounds, text вҖ” a red |\n30: | Ink 3 | `#0f1011` | `--color-ink-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |\n31: | Crimson 3 | `#ff0000` | `--color-crimson-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a red |\n32: | Azure | `#6d78d5` | `--color-azure` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n33: | Voltage 3 | `#27a644` | `--color-voltage-3` | borders, text вҖ” a green |\n34: | Azure 2 | `#6366f1` | `--color-azure-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a blue |\n35: | Obsidian 2 | `#323334` | `--color-obsidian-2` | borders, icons вҖ” a deep near-black |\n36: | Teal 2 | `#02b8cc` | `--color-teal-2` | backgrounds, icons вҖ” a teal |\n37: | Azure 3 | `#5e6ad2` | `--color-azure-3` | backgrounds, icons вҖ” a blue |\n38: | Indigo | `#8b5cf6` | `--color-indigo` | backgrounds вҖ” a indigo |\n39: | Obsidian 3 | `#28282c` | `--color-obsidian-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n40: | Light Azure 3 | `#b2d5ff` | `--color-light-azure-3` | gradients вҖ” a light blue |\n41: | Light Indigo | `#dfd1ff` | `--color-light-indigo` | gradients вҖ” a light indigo |\n42: | Steel 2 | `#9c9da1` | `--color-steel-2` | icons, backgrounds вҖ” a light gray |\n43: | Obsidian 4 | `#161718` | `--color-obsidian-4` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n44: | Teal 3 | `#10b981` | `--color-teal-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a teal |\n45: | Deep Teal | `#0f3338` | `--color-deep-teal` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep teal |\n46: | Deep Crimson | `#422222` | `--color-deep-crimson` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep red |\n47: | Citron | `#e4f222` | `--color-citron` | backgrounds вҖ” a yellow |\n48: | Slate 2 | `#5b5c5a` | `--color-slate-2` | icons вҖ” a mid gray |\n49: | Crimson 4 | `#e3484e` | `--color-crimson-4` | icons вҖ” a red |\n50: | Ember 2 | `#ff7236` | `--color-ember-2` | icons вҖ” a orange |\n51: | Azure 4 | `#4354b8` | `--color-azure-4` | icons вҖ” a blue |\n52: | Ember 3 | `#e5591d` | `--color-ember-3` | icons вҖ” a orange |\n53: | Slate 3 | `#808080` | `--color-slate-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a mid gray |\n54: | Graphite 2 | `#505050` | `--color-graphite-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a dark gray |\n55: \n56: ## Tokens вҖ” Typography\n57: \n58: ### Inter Variable вҖ” the entire interface, caption to hero В· `--font-inter`\n59: - **Substitute:** Inter, system sans-serif\n60: - **Weights:** 400, 510, 590 (loaded as a 100вҖ“900 variable axis)\n61: - **Sizes:** 10px, 11px, 12px, 13px, 14px, 15px, 16px, 17px, 20px, 24px, 32px, 48px, 64px, 72px\n62: - **Line height:** 15px through 72px, tracking each size 1.2вҖ“1.5Г—\n63: - **Letter spacing:** tightens with size вҖ” normal at the small UI sizes, -0.182px at 14px, -0.704px at 32px, down to -1.584px at the largest heading\n64: - **Role:** Sole UI, body, label, navigation, and headline typeface. The three weights do strict duty вҖ” 400 for body and reading, 510 for UI and interactive labels, 590 for headings and emphasis.\n65: \n66: ### Berkeley Mono вҖ” code and technical labels В· `--font-berkeley-mono`\n67: - **Substitute:** Fira Code, JetBrains Mono, monospace\n68: - **Weights:** 400 (loaded as a 100вҖ“900 variable axis)\n69: - **Sizes:** 12px (the code-block size)\n70: - **Role:** Reserved for inline code, code blocks, and technical fragments. It is the only break from Inter Variable in the system, marking machine text as distinct from prose.\n71: \n72: ### Type Scale\n73: \n74: | Role | Size | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Token |\n75: |------|------|-------------|----------------|-------|\n76: | caption | 10px | 15px | -0.15px | `--text-caption` |\n77: | caption-strong | 11px | 15.4px | normal | `--text-caption-strong` |\n78: | body-sm | 12px | 16.8px | normal | `--text-body-sm` |\n79: | body | 13px | 19.5px | -0.13px | `--text-body` |\n80: | body-md | 14px | 21px | -0.182px | `--text-body-md` |\n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 592. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Linear вҖ” Style Reference\n> A near-black product canvas where content surfaces through luminance, and a single indigo is the only thing allowed to glow.\n\n**Theme:** dark\n\nLinear builds on a near-black canvas (`#08090a`), against which Snow text (`#f7f8f8`) sits at 19.74:1 contrast вҖ” the dominant pairing across the entire surface. Inter Variable carries every word, ranging from a 10px caption to a 72px hero, with hierarchy driven by tracking that tightens as size grows (-0.15px at 10px down to -1.584px at the largest heading). Colour is rationed hard: most of the 43 tokens are achromatic grays stepping from Snow through Steel (`#8a8f98`) and Slate (`#62666d`) to the Ink near-blacks, and Azure 3 (`#5e6ad2`) is the one indigo reserved for the brand accent and badges. Surfaces are not painted in вҖ” interactive elements are built from near-transparent white overlays (`rgba(255,255,255,0.01)` to `0.05`) that only resolve into panels through hairline borders and a deep 16-token shadow stack. Layout runs edge to edge at 100% width with section spacing that swings from 48px up past 200px, framing each block as a self-contained slab. Berkeley Mono handles code, the one place the system leaves its sans-serif voice.\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n\n| Name | Value | Token | Role |\n|------|-------|-------|------|\n| Snow | `#f7f8f8` | `--color-snow` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a near-white |\n| Slate | `#62666d` | `--color-slate` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a mid gray |\n| Light Azure | `#d0d6e0` | `--color-light-azure` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a light blue |\n| Steel | `#8a8f98` | `--color-steel` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a light gray |\n| Linen | `#e2e4e7` | `--color-linen` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a soft off-white |\n| Light Magenta | `#f79ce0` | `--color-light-magenta` | borders, text вҖ” a light magenta |\n| Obsidian | `#202122` | `--color-obsidian` | borders, gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Teal | `#55cdff` | `--color-teal` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a teal |\n| Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/linear/DESIGN.md","text":"# Linear вҖ” Style Reference\n> A near-black product canvas where content surfaces through luminance, and a single indigo is the only thing allowed to glow.\n\n**Theme:** dark\n\nLinear builds on a near-black canvas (`#08090a`), against which Snow text (`#f7f8f8`) sits at 19.74:1 contrast вҖ” the dominant pairing across the entire surface. Inter Variable carries every word, ranging from a 10px caption to a 72px hero, with hierarchy driven by tracking that tightens as size grows (-0.15px at 10px down to -1.584px at the largest heading). Colour is rationed hard: most of the 43 tokens are achromatic grays stepping from Snow through Steel (`#8a8f98`) and Slate (`#62666d`) to the Ink near-blacks, and Azure 3 (`#5e6ad2`) is the one indigo reserved for the brand accent and badges. Surfaces are not painted in вҖ” interactive elements are built from near-transparent white overlays (`rgba(255,255,255,0.01)` to `0.05`) that only resolve into panels through hairline borders and a deep 16-token shadow stack. Layout runs edge to edge at 100% width with section spacing that swings from 48px up past 200px, framing each block as a self-contained slab. Berkeley Mono handles code, the one place the system leaves its sans-serif voice.\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Colors\n\n| Name | Value | Token | Role |\n|------|-------|-------|------|\n| Snow | `#f7f8f8` | `--color-snow` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a near-white |\n| Slate | `#62666d` | `--color-slate` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a mid gray |\n| Light Azure | `#d0d6e0` | `--color-light-azure` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a light blue |\n| Steel | `#8a8f98` | `--color-steel` | borders, text, icons вҖ” a light gray |\n| Linen | `#e2e4e7` | `--color-linen` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a soft off-white |\n| Light Magenta | `#f79ce0` | `--color-light-magenta` | borders, text вҖ” a light magenta |\n| Obsidian | `#202122` | `--color-obsidian` | borders, gradients, backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Teal | `#55cdff` | `--color-teal` | borders, text, backgrounds вҖ” a teal |\n| Ink | `#000000` | `--color-ink` | backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |\n| Ink 2 | `#08090a` | `--color-ink-2` | text, borders, backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |\n| Ember | `#ffc47c` | `--color-ember` | borders, text вҖ” a orange |\n| Light Azure 2 | `#8fa4ff` | `--color-light-azure-2` | borders, text вҖ” a light blue |\n| Sage | `#89d196` | `--color-sage` | borders, text вҖ” a green-gray |\n| Voltage | `#00ff05` | `--color-voltage` | backgrounds вҖ” a green |\n| Graphite | `#383b3f` | `--color-graphite` | borders, backgrounds, icons вҖ” a dark gray |\n| Crimson | `#d6303d` | `--color-crimson` | text, borders вҖ” a red |\n| Voltage 2 | `#008d2c` | `--color-voltage-2` | text, borders вҖ” a green |\n| Crimson 2 | `#eb5757` | `--color-crimson-2` | borders, backgrounds, text вҖ” a red |\n| Ink 3 | `#0f1011` | `--color-ink-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a near-black |\n| Crimson 3 | `#ff0000` | `--color-crimson-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a red |\n| Azure | `#6d78d5` | `--color-azure` | borders, text вҖ” a blue |\n| Voltage 3 | `#27a644` | `--color-voltage-3` | borders, text вҖ” a green |\n| Azure 2 | `#6366f1` | `--color-azure-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a blue |\n| Obsidian 2 | `#323334` | `--color-obsidian-2` | borders, icons вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Teal 2 | `#02b8cc` | `--color-teal-2` | backgrounds, icons вҖ” a teal |\n| Azure 3 | `#5e6ad2` | `--color-azure-3` | backgrounds, icons вҖ” a blue |\n| Indigo | `#8b5cf6` | `--color-indigo` | backgrounds вҖ” a indigo |\n| Obsidian 3 | `#28282c` | `--color-obsidian-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Light Azure 3 | `#b2d5ff` | `--color-light-azure-3` | gradients вҖ” a light blue |\n| Light Indigo | `#dfd1ff` | `--color-light-indigo` | gradients вҖ” a light indigo |\n| Steel 2 | `#9c9da1` | `--color-steel-2` | icons, backgrounds вҖ” a light gray |\n| Obsidian 4 | `#161718` | `--color-obsidian-4` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep near-black |\n| Teal 3 | `#10b981` | `--color-teal-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a teal |\n| Deep Teal | `#0f3338` | `--color-deep-teal` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep teal |\n| Deep Crimson | `#422222` | `--color-deep-crimson` | backgrounds вҖ” a deep red |\n| Citron | `#e4f222` | `--color-citron` | backgrounds вҖ” a yellow |\n| Slate 2 | `#5b5c5a` | `--color-slate-2` | icons вҖ” a mid gray |\n| Crimson 4 | `#e3484e` | `--color-crimson-4` | icons вҖ” a red |\n| Ember 2 | `#ff7236` | `--color-ember-2` | icons вҖ” a orange |\n| Azure 4 | `#4354b8` | `--color-azure-4` | icons вҖ” a blue |\n| Ember 3 | `#e5591d` | `--color-ember-3` | icons вҖ” a orange |\n| Slate 3 | `#808080` | `--color-slate-3` | backgrounds вҖ” a mid gray |\n| Graphite 2 | `#505050` | `--color-graphite-2` | backgrounds вҖ” a dark gray |\n\n## Tokens вҖ” Typography\n\n### Inter Variable вҖ” the entire interface, caption to hero В· `--font-inter`\n- **Substitute:** Inter, system sans-serif\n- **Weights:** 400, 510, 590 (loaded as a 100вҖ“900 variable axis)\n- **Sizes:** 10px, 11px, 12px, 13px, 14px, 15px, 16px, 17px, 20px, 24px, 32px, 48px, 64px, 72px\n- **Line height:** 15px through 72px, tracking each size 1.2вҖ“1.5Г—\n- **Letter spacing:** tightens with size вҖ” normal at the small UI sizes, -0.182px at 14px, -0.704px at 32px, down to -1.584px at the largest heading\n- **Role:** Sole UI, body, label, navigation, and headline typeface. The three weights do strict duty вҖ” 400 for body and reading, 510 for UI and interactive labels, 590 for headings and emphasis.\n\n### Berkeley Mono вҖ” code and technical labels В· `--font-berkeley-mono`\n- **Substitute:** Fira Code, JetBrains Mono, monospace\n- **Weights:** 400 (loaded as a 100вҖ“900 variable axis)\n- **Sizes:** 12px (the code-block size)\n- **Role:** Reserved for inline code, code blocks, and technical fragments. It is the only break from Inter Variable in the system, marking machine text as distinct from prose.\n\n### Type Scale\n\n| Role | Size | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Token |\n|------|------|-------------|----------------|-------|\n| caption | 10px | 15px | -0.15px | `--text-caption` |\n| caption-strong | 11px | 15.4px | normal | `--text-caption-strong` |\n| body-sm | 12px | 16.8px | normal | `--text-body-sm` |\n| body | 13px | 19.5px | -0.13px | `--text-body` |\n| body-md | 14px | 21px | -0.182px | `--text-body-md` |","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":592,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/examples/linear/DESIGN.md","time":{"start":1782532433603,"end":1782532433632}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f9f392428e18d6d016a3f495163e881948c3e4bd7d3b5f182"}},"id":"prt_f073666be0019uLYTgySOitR7g","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","messageID":"msg_f073583cf001yFIFOrufYdGerR"}}
