{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782532435922,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","part":{"id":"prt_f07366fd1001LdKlGPbm6U0xPq","messageID":"msg_f07366a63001JNlukPamrlszMN","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","snapshot":"11dee8000c43883a585e97ac816b4c510dbb9265","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532447667,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5HUsY3pRCWLbIROd13nmsqTV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests/README.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"tests: Vitest Unit Suite for the Extraction Pipeline\"\n3: description: \"Vitest unit coverage for the backend pipeline: OKLCH clustering, deterministic v3 emitters, the validation engine, prompt building, accessibility extraction and CLI flag parsing.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"md-generator tests\"\n6:   - \"backend vitest suite\"\n7:   - \"design pipeline unit tests\"\n8:   - \"cluster validate formatters tests\"\n9: ---\n10: \n11: # tests: Vitest Unit Suite for the Extraction Pipeline\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n16: \n17: `tests/` owns the vitest unit suite for the backend extraction pipeline. Each file imports its subject from `../scripts/` and asserts current behavior of one module, from raw colour parsing through the deterministic DESIGN.md emitters and the validation engine.\n18: \n19: Current state:\n20: \n21: - 7 test files, 68 tests, run by vitest.\n22: - Every file imports its subject directly from `../scripts/` (for example `from '../scripts/cluster'`).\n23: - `cluster.test.ts` is the largest suite at 42 tests covering colour parsing, contrast, OKLCH delta-E, shadow classification and token merging.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## 2. DIRECTORY TREE\n28: \n29: ```text\n30: tests/\n31: +-- cluster.test.ts            # OKLCH clustering, parsing, contrast, delta-E, shadow + token merge\n32: +-- cluster-classify.test.ts   # classifyVariant and classifyColorStability\n33: +-- formatters-v3.test.ts      # deterministic v3 emitters, colour namer, max-width verbatim rule\n34: +-- validate.test.ts           # validation engine, hex accuracy, prose fabrication, sections\n35: +-- build-write-prompt.test.ts # v3 pre-render, FACTS block, prose-only write prompt\n36: +-- a11y-extract.test.ts       # accessibility extraction, focus honest absence\n37: +-- parseargs.test.ts          # extract.ts flag parsing, order independence, --fast defaults\n38: `-- README.md\n39: ```\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ## 3. KEY FILES\n44: \n45: | File | Responsibility |\n46: |---|---|\n47: | `cluster.test.ts` | Covers `parseColor`, `parsePxValue`, `rgbaToHex`, `wcagContrast`, `deltaE`, `splitShadowLayers`, `classifyShadow` and `mergeTokenSets`. Asserts OKLCH delta-E within-cluster thresholds and L1 to L4 token merging by perceptual identity. |\n48: | `cluster-classify.test.ts` | Covers the extracted `classifyVariant` button heuristic across every branch including Outline and Tertiary, plus `classifyColorStability` capping a high-frequency single-page colour at the campaign layer through the coverage gate. |\n49: | `formatters-v3.test.ts` | Covers the deterministic v3 emitters: `nameColors` hue and lightness naming with collision suffixes, the fab-killer rule where `formatSpacingShapesV3` emits `100%` max-width verbatim, deterministic `emitQuickStart`, and clean empty-token rendering. |\n50: | `validate.test.ts` | Covers `validateDesignMd`: hex accuracy, phantom-colour and content-layer detection, Quick Start fidelity, prose-fabrication warnings, section completeness and the failure and warning scoring math. |\n51: | `build-write-prompt.test.ts` | Covers `buildWritePrompt`: the deterministic v3 pre-render, the FACTS block, the flat-elevation rule for zero shadows and focus-honesty wording driven by captured and consistent flags. |\n52: | `a11y-extract.test.ts` | Covers `extractA11y` focus-indicator honesty: `captured:false` and `consistent:false` on empty data, and a real captured outline style. |\n53: | `parseargs.test.ts` | Covers `parseArgs` from `extract.ts`: order-independent `--fast`, `--fast` defaults applied only without an explicit value, and interaction capture defaulting on. |\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 4. BOUNDARIES AND FLOW\n58: \n59: | Boundary | Rule |\n60: |---|---|\n61: | Imports | Each test imports its subject from `../scripts/` and shared types from `../scripts/types`. |\n62: | Build | The suite is type-checked by `tsconfig.json`, which includes `tests/**/*`. `tsconfig.build.json` excludes `tests` and `**/*.test.ts`, so tests never reach the `dist` emit. |\n63: | Discovery | `vitest.config.ts` sets `include: ['tests/**/*.test.ts']`, so vitest discovers every `.test.ts` under this folder. |\n64: \n65: Main flow:\n66: \n67: ```text\n68: в•ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•®\n69: в”Ӯ npm test (vitest run)                    в”Ӯ\n70: в•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•Ҝ\n71:                   в”Ӯ\n72:                   в–ј\n73: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n74: в”Ӯ vitest.config.ts include glob            в”Ӯ\n75: в”Ӯ tests/**/*.test.ts                       в”Ӯ\n76: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n77:                   в”Ӯ\n78:                   в–ј\n79: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n80: в”Ӯ each *.test.ts imports from ../scripts/  в”Ӯ\n81: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n82:                   в”Ӯ\n83:                   в–ј\n84: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n85: в”Ӯ assertions on the pipeline modules       в”Ӯ\n86: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n87:                   в”Ӯ\n88:                   в–ј\n89: в•ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•®\n90: в”Ӯ 7 files, 68 tests, pass or fail report   в”Ӯ\n91: в•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•Ҝ\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## 5. VALIDATION\n97: \n98: Run from the `backend/` directory.\n99: \n100: ```bash\n101: npm test\n102: ```\n103: \n104: Expected result:\n105: \n106: ```text\n107:  Test Files  7 passed (7)\n108:       Tests  68 passed (68)\n109: ```\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 6. RELATED\n114: \n115: - [`backend README`](../README.md)\n116: - [`scripts README`](../scripts/README.md)\n117: - [`md-generator SKILL`](../../SKILL.md)\n\n(End of file - total 117 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"tests: Vitest Unit Suite for the Extraction Pipeline\"\ndescription: \"Vitest unit coverage for the backend pipeline: OKLCH clustering, deterministic v3 emitters, the validation engine, prompt building, accessibility extraction and CLI flag parsing.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"md-generator tests\"\n  - \"backend vitest suite\"\n  - \"design pipeline unit tests\"\n  - \"cluster validate formatters tests\"\n---\n\n# tests: Vitest Unit Suite for the Extraction Pipeline\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n`tests/` owns the vitest unit suite for the backend extraction pipeline. Each file imports its subject from `../scripts/` and asserts current behavior of one module, from raw colour parsing through the deterministic DESIGN.md emitters and the validation engine.\n\nCurrent state:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests/README.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"tests: Vitest Unit Suite for the Extraction Pipeline\"\ndescription: \"Vitest unit coverage for the backend pipeline: OKLCH clustering, deterministic v3 emitters, the validation engine, prompt building, accessibility extraction and CLI flag parsing.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"md-generator tests\"\n  - \"backend vitest suite\"\n  - \"design pipeline unit tests\"\n  - \"cluster validate formatters tests\"\n---\n\n# tests: Vitest Unit Suite for the Extraction Pipeline\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n`tests/` owns the vitest unit suite for the backend extraction pipeline. Each file imports its subject from `../scripts/` and asserts current behavior of one module, from raw colour parsing through the deterministic DESIGN.md emitters and the validation engine.\n\nCurrent state:\n\n- 7 test files, 68 tests, run by vitest.\n- Every file imports its subject directly from `../scripts/` (for example `from '../scripts/cluster'`).\n- `cluster.test.ts` is the largest suite at 42 tests covering colour parsing, contrast, OKLCH delta-E, shadow classification and token merging.\n\n---\n\n## 2. DIRECTORY TREE\n\n```text\ntests/\n+-- cluster.test.ts            # OKLCH clustering, parsing, contrast, delta-E, shadow + token merge\n+-- cluster-classify.test.ts   # classifyVariant and classifyColorStability\n+-- formatters-v3.test.ts      # deterministic v3 emitters, colour namer, max-width verbatim rule\n+-- validate.test.ts           # validation engine, hex accuracy, prose fabrication, sections\n+-- build-write-prompt.test.ts # v3 pre-render, FACTS block, prose-only write prompt\n+-- a11y-extract.test.ts       # accessibility extraction, focus honest absence\n+-- parseargs.test.ts          # extract.ts flag parsing, order independence, --fast defaults\n`-- README.md\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. KEY FILES\n\n| File | Responsibility |\n|---|---|\n| `cluster.test.ts` | Covers `parseColor`, `parsePxValue`, `rgbaToHex`, `wcagContrast`, `deltaE`, `splitShadowLayers`, `classifyShadow` and `mergeTokenSets`. Asserts OKLCH delta-E within-cluster thresholds and L1 to L4 token merging by perceptual identity. |\n| `cluster-classify.test.ts` | Covers the extracted `classifyVariant` button heuristic across every branch including Outline and Tertiary, plus `classifyColorStability` capping a high-frequency single-page colour at the campaign layer through the coverage gate. |\n| `formatters-v3.test.ts` | Covers the deterministic v3 emitters: `nameColors` hue and lightness naming with collision suffixes, the fab-killer rule where `formatSpacingShapesV3` emits `100%` max-width verbatim, deterministic `emitQuickStart`, and clean empty-token rendering. |\n| `validate.test.ts` | Covers `validateDesignMd`: hex accuracy, phantom-colour and content-layer detection, Quick Start fidelity, prose-fabrication warnings, section completeness and the failure and warning scoring math. |\n| `build-write-prompt.test.ts` | Covers `buildWritePrompt`: the deterministic v3 pre-render, the FACTS block, the flat-elevation rule for zero shadows and focus-honesty wording driven by captured and consistent flags. |\n| `a11y-extract.test.ts` | Covers `extractA11y` focus-indicator honesty: `captured:false` and `consistent:false` on empty data, and a real captured outline style. |\n| `parseargs.test.ts` | Covers `parseArgs` from `extract.ts`: order-independent `--fast`, `--fast` defaults applied only without an explicit value, and interaction capture defaulting on. |\n\n---\n\n## 4. BOUNDARIES AND FLOW\n\n| Boundary | Rule |\n|---|---|\n| Imports | Each test imports its subject from `../scripts/` and shared types from `../scripts/types`. |\n| Build | The suite is type-checked by `tsconfig.json`, which includes `tests/**/*`. `tsconfig.build.json` excludes `tests` and `**/*.test.ts`, so tests never reach the `dist` emit. |\n| Discovery | `vitest.config.ts` sets `include: ['tests/**/*.test.ts']`, so vitest discovers every `.test.ts` under this folder. |\n\nMain flow:\n\n```text\nв•ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•®\nв”Ӯ npm test (vitest run)                    в”Ӯ\nв•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•Ҝ\n                  в”Ӯ\n                  в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ vitest.config.ts include glob            в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ tests/**/*.test.ts                       в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                  в”Ӯ\n                  в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ each *.test.ts imports from ../scripts/  в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                  в”Ӯ\n                  в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ assertions on the pipeline modules       в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                  в”Ӯ\n                  в–ј\nв•ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•®\nв”Ӯ 7 files, 68 tests, pass or fail report   в”Ӯ\nв•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•Ҝ\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. VALIDATION\n\nRun from the `backend/` directory.\n\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\n\nExpected result:\n\n```text\n Test Files  7 passed (7)\n      Tests  68 passed (68)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED\n\n- [`backend README`](../README.md)\n- [`scripts README`](../scripts/README.md)\n- [`md-generator SKILL`](../../SKILL.md)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":117,"totalLines":117,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests/README.md","time":{"start":1782532447661,"end":1782532447666}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0be6b44a5446aaf5016a3f495f9ae88191836ec8eb5eca2dde"}},"id":"prt_f07369d7e001cRdrtqx9epOLZo","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","messageID":"msg_f07366a63001JNlukPamrlszMN"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532447729,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffe3IWN2NyShq3kW9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_alLQ4lkR6YdEkDTafAYYygcb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"parseArgs|--fast|quickstart|section|stability|content-color|claimsScore|validateDesignMd","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests","include":"*.ts"},"output":"Found 48 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests/parseargs.test.ts:\n  Line 2: import { parseArgs } from '../scripts/extract';\n\n  Line 4: // parseArgs takes process.argv form (it slices the leading [node, script]).\n\n  Line 5: const pa = (...a: string[]) => parseArgs(['node', 'extract', ...a]);\n\n  Line 7: // Regression coverage for the flag-handling fixes: order-independent --fast (never\n\n  Line 9: describe('parseArgs flag handling', () => {\n\n  Line 10:   it('--fast does NOT clobber an explicit --max-pages/--concurrency (order-independent)', () => {\n\n  Line 11:     expect(pa('https://x.com', '--max-pages', '10', '--fast').maxPages).toBe(10);\n\n  Line 12:     expect(pa('https://x.com', '--fast', '--max-pages', '10').maxPages).toBe(10);\n\n  Line 13:     expect(pa('https://x.com', '--fast', '--concurrency', '3').concurrency).toBe(3);\n\n  Line 16:   it('--fast applies its defaults only when no explicit value is given', () => {\n\n  Line 17:     expect(pa('https://x.com', '--fast').maxPages).toBe(5);\n\n  Line 18:     expect(pa('https://x.com', '--fast').concurrency).toBe(8);\n\n  Line 21:   it('interaction capture is default-ON; --fast still captures; --fast-no-interaction opts out', () => {\n\n  Line 23:     expect(pa('https://x.com', '--fast').noInteraction).toBe(false);\n\n  Line 24:     const fni = pa('https://x.com', '--fast-no-interaction');\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_E